The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Lanka

 Colombo, Jan. 22 (Reuters): Suspected Tamil Tiger rebels shot and injured four Sri Lankan troops in an ambush in the islands restive east, police said on Sunday ? the eve of a peace initiative aimed at averting a slide back to civil war.

 The attack in the eastern district of Batticaloa came hours after a police constable was injured by a grenade in the latest violence that has strained a 2002 truce to breaking point.

 The LTTE said the blasts occurred during a training exercise and no one was hurt.




